The '''Stark Commercial Combine''', also called the '''Stark Collective''' or '''Stark Commerce Combine''', was a criminal conglomeration of [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] and [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]] in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]. It was organized, led by, and named after [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Iaco Stark/Legends|Iaco Stark]]. Its flagship was the [[Raptor (starship)|''Raptor'']].

==History==
Secretly in league with scheming dignitaries in the governing boards of the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] and the [[Xucphra Corporation]], the Collective caused the [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] shortage of [[44 BBY/Legends|44 BBY]]. During it, the Combine became heroes to the poor people of the Outer Rim when they began "raiding" bacta shipments
and redirecting them to the planets that otherwise could not afford them - although still selling it at a profit to benefit their alliance with the Trade Federation.

Members of the [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] suspected that the Collective was behind the bacta shortage, and along with representatives of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] agreed to Stark's suggestion of a mediation summit on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Troiken/Legends|Troiken]]. However, it was a trap; the Collective had developed a [[Navcomputer virus|navicomputer virus]] and unleashed it on the illegal [[Outland Regions Security Force/Legends|war fleet]] assembled by [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Ranulph Tarkin/Legends|Ranulph Tarkin]], resulting in the [[Stark Hyperspace War/Legends|Stark Hyperspace War]].

The Combine was defeated in the war when the Jedi intervened after convincing the Trade Federation to turn on their allies. Xucphra Corporation's duplicity was discovered and resulted in it being kicked off of [[Thyferra/Legends|Thyferra]], while Stark killed his Combine co-directors in a bid to defect to the the side of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] on positive terms (which he did). The remnants of the Collective surrendered following the [[Fifth Battle of Qotile]], and Stark himself eventually found a job as a legitimate businessman for the [[Commerce Guild/Legends|Commerce Guild]].

